00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:18,940 --> 00:00:23,880
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

2
00:00:25,290 --> 00:00:29,260
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

3
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:37,010
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

4
00:00:38,210 --> 00:00:43,120
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

5
00:00:44,650 --> 00:00:47,930
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

6
00:00:47,930 --> 00:00:51,000
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

7
00:00:51,710 --> 00:00:56,660
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

8
00:00:57,700 --> 00:01:00,880
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

9
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:04,160
♪The open sky rises high♪

10
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:09,830
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

11
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:13,860
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

12
00:01:13,860 --> 00:01:17,220
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

13
00:01:17,630 --> 00:01:23,300
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

14
00:01:23,710 --> 00:01:26,960
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

15
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:30,290
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

16
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:34,730
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

17
00:01:34,730 --> 00:01:35,980
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 20=

19
00:02:37,850 --> 00:02:38,710
Troupe Leader.

20
00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:41,040
Still up this late?

21
00:02:41,320 --> 00:02:42,880
Aren't you the same?

22
00:02:42,880 --> 00:02:44,280
Hard to sleep alone.

23
00:02:46,320 --> 00:02:47,280
Let's chat then.

24
00:02:51,160 --> 00:02:52,600
People are strange creatures.

25
00:02:53,680 --> 00:02:55,600
Before, I wanted to leave
this place, but couldn't.

26
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:57,960
Now that I can leave,

27
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:00,400
I suddenly feel lost.

28
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:03,040
What's there to feel lost about?

29
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:06,000
The troupe is your home.

30
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:08,160
Come back and visit at any time.

31
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:12,680
I won't come back here again.

32
00:03:14,160 --> 00:03:15,600
I'm not welcome here.

33
00:03:16,640 --> 00:03:18,240
Who said that?

34
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:19,600
You're more than welcome here.

35
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:24,680
I know where I stand.

36
00:03:29,080 --> 00:03:29,920
Zhu.

37
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:33,920
You've been through a lot over the years.

38
00:03:35,760 --> 00:03:37,160
What are you talking about?

39
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:38,480
Not at all.

40
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,160
Do you believe in fate?

41
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:57,760
Life

42
00:03:58,360 --> 00:03:59,760
is just a game of chess.

43
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:03,920
And we're just the pieces.

44
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:07,920
How the pieces move

45
00:04:07,920 --> 00:04:09,880
is all predetermined.

46
00:04:09,880 --> 00:04:11,000
If you play the knight,

47
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,320
you can only move in an L-shape.

48
00:04:12,320 --> 00:04:13,240
If I play the bishop,

49
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:14,800
I can only move diagonally.

50
00:04:16,280 --> 00:04:17,840
There's no other choice.

51
00:04:19,520 --> 00:04:20,360
Right.

52
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:21,600
You are right.

53
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:25,920
Zhu.

54
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:27,640
All you ever say

55
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:29,240
to me is just "right".

56
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:31,920
Right about what?

57
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:35,480
If I had a notebook, I'd write it down.

58
00:04:43,140 --> 00:04:45,260
(Hongqi)

59
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:50,720
I'll leave this notebook for you too.

60
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:54,840
Hope it helps with your work.

61
00:04:56,760 --> 00:04:58,560
Focus on the issue, not the person.

62
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:03,440
Right.

63
00:05:04,260 --> 00:05:07,540
(Xinhua Dictionary)

64
00:06:18,580 --> 00:06:19,940
(Qinqiang Opera Troupe)

65
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:37,800
Come back and visit when you have time.

66
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:39,760
I will.

67
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:42,360
Please take care.

68
00:06:52,320 --> 00:06:53,200
Stay strong.

69
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:56,160
Keep singing.

70
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:00,320
Yi Qing'e,

71
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:03,440
you'll be a big star someday.

72
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:17,720
Back then, your uncle

73
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:19,640
entrusted you to my care.

74
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:24,920
But I can't protect you anymore.

75
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:27,400
You must protect yourself now.

76
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:55,200
Mi Lan left.

77
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:57,400
She went to the distant south.

78
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:00,280
Watching the car drive away,

79
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:02,920
Yi Qing'e suddenly realized

80
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:05,760
the place she found outside Jiuyangou

81
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:09,040
was the very mountain trapping Mi Lan.

82
00:08:11,910 --> 00:08:12,760
Go.

83
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:13,960
It's uphill. I'll get off first.

84
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:15,640
- Okay. Easy now.
- Let me help.

85
00:08:15,640 --> 00:08:17,240
- I'm fine.
- Let's go.

86
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:18,400
One, two, go!

87
00:08:18,400 --> 00:08:19,960
Come on, lend a hand.

88
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:21,400
Master Gou.

89
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:24,120
Thank you!

90
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:25,200
Goodbye.

91
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:26,720
Goodbye. Master Gou, goodbye.

92
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:27,560
Goodbye.

93
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:43,280
Who is it?

94
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:52,760
(Entrance Guard)
Huang Zhengjing also left.

95
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:55,880
He left empty-handed.

96
00:08:56,920 --> 00:08:58,280
Not a single thing from the troupe

97
00:08:58,280 --> 00:08:59,480
did he take with him.

98
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:02,560
A tricycle and a bicycle

99
00:09:02,560 --> 00:09:04,840
carried away all his belongings.

100
00:09:05,520 --> 00:09:07,240
Yi Qing'e just didn't expect that

101
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:09,480
the one lighting firecrackers

102
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:11,560
was his most trusted

103
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:13,400
Head of Security Section.

104
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:22,120
The higher-ups made me

105
00:09:22,920 --> 00:09:24,400
the acting Troupe Director.

106
00:09:26,320 --> 00:09:27,320
Acting?

107
00:09:29,040 --> 00:09:30,040
Temporarily acting.

108
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:34,000
The troupe is finally back in our hands.

109
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:35,800
Nonsense.

110
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:37,360
What does it have to do with us?

111
00:09:37,880 --> 00:09:40,560
The troupe is back in expert hands.

112
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:42,800
Trouple Leader Zhu,

113
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:44,520
congratulations.

114
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:49,000
Since you're the new boss now,

115
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,560
let's start rehearsing right away

116
00:09:50,560 --> 00:09:52,160
the full play of Yang Pai Feng,

117
00:09:52,640 --> 00:09:53,480
shall we?

118
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:55,000
We can't.

119
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:55,840
Why not?

120
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:58,440
Don't you call the shots in the troupe?

121
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:03,440
Huang Zhengjing was right.

122
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:05,800
That Da Jiao Zan was

123
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:09,080
like a stone stirring up a thousand waves.

124
00:10:09,520 --> 00:10:12,280
The response has been extremely strong.

125
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:21,640
Especially among the girls
in our trainee class.

126
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:23,480
Some of

127
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:26,160
their parents are local officials.

128
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:29,920
Regarding the kitchen girl Yi Qing'e

129
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:32,600
being the lead in Da Jiao Zan,

130
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:34,920
they're demanding answers.

131
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:36,200
And

132
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:38,760
they're also seriously questioning

133
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:40,080
why their girls,

134
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:42,000
after years of training,

135
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:44,280
are unable to get on stage.

136
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:45,480
For what?

137
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:47,040
What do you mean?

138
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:50,000
The troupe will keep rotting like this?

139
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:51,880
What kind of talk is that?

140
00:10:52,560 --> 00:10:55,400
We rot if we don't do Yang Pai Feng?

141
00:10:55,920 --> 00:10:57,400
I want Yang Men Nyu Jiang.

142
00:10:57,760 --> 00:10:59,360
You must be dreaming.

143
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:03,240
Let Trouple Leader Zhu finish speaking.

144
00:11:04,520 --> 00:11:06,400
Yang Men Nyu Jiang would be

145
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:08,320
a grand production.

146
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:11,160
It requires a lot of actors.

147
00:11:11,480 --> 00:11:14,200
Mu Guiying, Eighth Sister, Ninth Sister...

148
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:15,880
Just the Widow Army alone

149
00:11:15,880 --> 00:11:18,120
would give all the girls a chance

150
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:19,120
to perform.

151
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,960
First, we can resolve internal conflicts

152
00:11:22,240 --> 00:11:24,080
to give county leaders an explanation.

153
00:11:24,680 --> 00:11:25,600
Second,

154
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:28,880
all the actors in this play

155
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:31,920
will be elected from our trainee class.

156
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:33,760
Taking this opportunity

157
00:11:34,120 --> 00:11:36,760
to train new blood for our troupe,

158
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:37,920
so these kids

159
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:40,040
can see new hope for our troupe.

160
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:42,080
Trouple Leader Zhu,

161
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:44,080
you are living in a fantasy.

162
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:47,080
To turn these amateur kids

163
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:48,320
into true professionals,

164
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:50,000
how much effort

165
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:50,920
will that take?

166
00:11:51,760 --> 00:11:53,040
Plus, there is a catch.

167
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:56,000
These kids must be able
to endure hardship.

168
00:11:57,840 --> 00:11:59,240
You nailed it.

169
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:01,840
Yi Qing'e didn't suffer for nothing.

170
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:04,000
And these kids have seen it all.

171
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,040
I'm telling you,

172
00:12:05,040 --> 00:12:07,400
these kids are scrambling right now

173
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:08,920
to go work in the kitchen.

174
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:14,760
These kids have been training for years.

175
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:17,040
They do have some basic skills.

176
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:18,400
Let's encourage them,

177
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:19,360
give them a refresher,

178
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:21,000
and be strict with them.

179
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:23,120
I think it'll work out.

180
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:26,800
I agree.

181
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:28,520
It's settled then.

182
00:12:29,160 --> 00:12:31,120
You four go and think carefully about how

183
00:12:31,120 --> 00:12:32,000
to handle this.

184
00:12:32,240 --> 00:12:33,440
Then report back to me,

185
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:36,640
so I can report to the county leaders.

186
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:38,120
Then it's settled.

187
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:40,840
By the way,

188
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:45,160
I'll return Yi Qing'e to the trainee class.

189
00:12:45,160 --> 00:12:47,360
She'll live and train with the trainees.

190
00:12:47,880 --> 00:12:50,480
No need to teach her privately anymore.

191
00:12:50,480 --> 00:12:51,600
Most importantly,

192
00:12:52,080 --> 00:12:54,680
don't call each other master and apprentice.

193
00:12:54,680 --> 00:12:55,960
- Why?
- Why?

194
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:57,270
- Why?
- What do you mean why?

195
00:12:57,760 --> 00:12:59,600
Our trainee class has 28 kids.

196
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:01,000
They are all your students.

197
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:02,760
Treat them equally

198
00:13:02,760 --> 00:13:04,040
to avoid any new conflicts.

199
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:06,880
Show off your skills?

200
00:13:07,040 --> 00:13:08,040
Don't make too much.

201
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:10,240
Or the three of us can't finish it all.

202
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:12,680
Knife skills are crucial, you know?

203
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:14,000
Cutting potatoes...

204
00:13:16,680 --> 00:13:18,120
You're cutting so fast.

205
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:19,200
When did you practice this?

206
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:20,200
Being fast isn't enough.

207
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:21,120
Watch your hands

208
00:13:21,120 --> 00:13:23,560
and cut them evenly.

209
00:13:23,560 --> 00:13:24,400
You...

210
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,520
They're actually very even.

211
00:13:28,760 --> 00:13:30,000
I know why you said

212
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:31,480
you'd show off your skills to us.

213
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:34,280
The wok is already so hot.

214
00:13:34,280 --> 00:13:35,760
You need to add oil first.

215
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:37,920
Hot wok, cold oil.

216
00:13:38,640 --> 00:13:40,680
What kind of cooking method is that?

217
00:13:57,720 --> 00:13:59,240
Looking good.

218
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:07,680
Have a taste.

219
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:11,440
How is it?

220
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:12,600
Delicious, huh?

221
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:15,200
Attention, attention!

222
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:16,360
I have an announcement!

223
00:14:16,360 --> 00:14:17,520
Shut up.

224
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:18,400
Open your mouth.

225
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:20,240
Taste it.

226
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:22,600
Delicious.

227
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:23,680
You didn't cook it.

228
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:25,080
- Laidi cooked it.
- How is it?

229
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:25,970
I taught her!

230
00:14:26,320 --> 00:14:28,480
Can a lousy master teach a good student?

231
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:29,960
A lousy master like you

232
00:14:29,960 --> 00:14:31,360
can train such a good apprentice.

233
00:14:31,360 --> 00:14:32,960
What's so strange about that?

234
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:34,760
You're talking nonsense.

235
00:14:34,760 --> 00:14:35,920
You are talking nonsense.

236
00:14:36,760 --> 00:14:37,600
Kid.

237
00:14:39,160 --> 00:14:40,000
Great cooking.

238
00:14:40,920 --> 00:14:42,760
This is the first dish you cooked,

239
00:14:42,760 --> 00:14:44,720
and it's also your last.

240
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:46,160
What do you mean?

241
00:14:46,160 --> 00:14:47,000
What do you mean?

242
00:14:47,360 --> 00:14:48,760
The troupe has decided,

243
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,520
starting today,

244
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:53,360
you're back to the trainee class!

245
00:14:54,960 --> 00:14:56,480
Awesome!

246
00:14:57,320 --> 00:14:59,000
Qiu, that's good news!

247
00:15:00,160 --> 00:15:01,040
It's great!

248
00:15:01,040 --> 00:15:02,440
Stop posing there.

249
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:07,560
Laidi,

250
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:08,920
what's wrong?

251
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:10,040
I'm not going.

252
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:11,280
Why?

253
00:15:12,280 --> 00:15:13,520
I just don't want to.

254
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:14,400
I'm staying right here.

255
00:15:15,560 --> 00:15:17,200
You'd pass up such a great opportunity

256
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:18,480
and be stuck in the kitchen forever?

257
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:20,120
- Why's this kid so silly?
- Exactly.

258
00:15:20,120 --> 00:15:21,640
I'm not silly. I'm not going anywhere.

259
00:15:21,640 --> 00:15:23,880
No. It's the troupe's call, not yours.

260
00:15:23,880 --> 00:15:25,520
Why should I go wherever you tell me to?

261
00:15:25,520 --> 00:15:27,200
Why should I do whatever you say?

262
00:15:27,640 --> 00:15:28,480
I'm not going.

263
00:15:28,960 --> 00:15:30,080
I'd rather die than go.

264
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:32,760
I won't be bossed around anymore.

265
00:15:33,760 --> 00:15:36,680
Kid, you can't perform if you refuse!

266
00:15:36,680 --> 00:15:37,640
I'm not performing!

267
00:15:37,640 --> 00:15:38,600
I never wanted to!

268
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:39,680
I was forced!

269
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:41,360
I'll just tend the kitchen fire forever!

270
00:15:41,360 --> 00:15:46,020
(Boiled water)

271
00:15:46,720 --> 00:15:47,920
What is the kid thinking?

272
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:51,760
What the kid thinks,

273
00:15:53,760 --> 00:15:55,480
does anyone really care?

274
00:16:33,080 --> 00:16:34,280
I'm not going anywhere.

275
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:37,720
I'll stay in the kitchen.

276
00:16:37,720 --> 00:16:39,200
The kitchen is my home.

277
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:57,920
Master Song.

278
00:17:01,160 --> 00:17:02,200
Master Song.

279
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:06,160
Don't kick me out.

280
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,320
Please.

281
00:17:16,240 --> 00:17:18,000
Please, Master Song.

282
00:17:18,920 --> 00:17:19,760
Kid.

283
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:23,960
Singing opera

284
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:26,200
is your true calling.

285
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:31,640
I don't want to leave.

286
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:35,400
I don't want to leave

287
00:17:36,660 --> 00:17:42,020
(Men; Boiled water)

288
00:17:43,440 --> 00:17:44,600
Did you talk to the kid?

289
00:17:44,960 --> 00:17:46,120
I did.

290
00:17:46,920 --> 00:17:48,640
She reacted very strongly.

291
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:50,600
She'd rather quit singing

292
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:51,840
than leave the kitchen.

293
00:17:52,040 --> 00:17:53,680
Qing'e must return to the trainee class.

294
00:17:53,680 --> 00:17:54,840
This is non-negotiable.

295
00:17:55,280 --> 00:17:56,120
Why?

296
00:17:56,310 --> 00:17:57,160
Why?

297
00:17:57,160 --> 00:17:58,400
I told you the reason.

298
00:17:58,680 --> 00:17:59,880
No wiggle room?

299
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:01,080
Wiggle room for what?

300
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:02,120
It's for her own good.

301
00:18:02,120 --> 00:18:03,320
More like for your own good.

302
00:18:03,320 --> 00:18:04,520
What good will I get?

303
00:18:04,520 --> 00:18:05,600
What good?

304
00:18:05,880 --> 00:18:07,840
So you can give everyone an explanation.

305
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:10,640
I'm the acting Troupe Director now.

306
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:13,160
Of course, I must consider all sides.

307
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:14,840
What are you scoffing at?

308
00:18:14,840 --> 00:18:16,240
We sent away one Huang Zhengjing,

309
00:18:16,600 --> 00:18:18,240
only to get a Zhu Zhengjing.

310
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:19,800
- What do you mean?
- What do I mean?

311
00:18:20,120 --> 00:18:22,640
Huang Zhengjing made her leave the class.

312
00:18:22,640 --> 00:18:24,920
Now you insist she go back to the class.

313
00:18:24,920 --> 00:18:26,440
What's the difference between you two?

314
00:18:26,440 --> 00:18:27,280
How is that the same?

315
00:18:27,280 --> 00:18:28,120
How is it different?

316
00:18:28,320 --> 00:18:29,960
You both just want to avoid trouble.

317
00:18:29,960 --> 00:18:31,440
Who ever considered the kid's feelings?

318
00:18:51,920 --> 00:18:54,080
So, why won't she go back to the class?

319
00:18:56,360 --> 00:18:57,200
Why?

320
00:18:58,360 --> 00:19:00,440
She's looked down on in the trainee class.

321
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:02,120
Always living at the mercy of others.

322
00:19:02,960 --> 00:19:05,360
Who knows how much she has suffered?

323
00:19:06,040 --> 00:19:08,800
She only feels warm in the kitchen.

324
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:11,160
She only feels safe when sleeping

325
00:19:11,160 --> 00:19:12,520
in that storeroom.

326
00:19:13,320 --> 00:19:15,120
Now you want to take the only

327
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:17,080
sense of security she has?

328
00:19:17,080 --> 00:19:18,280
How will she survive?

329
00:19:20,760 --> 00:19:21,600
Besides,

330
00:19:22,040 --> 00:19:23,520
we are her masters.

331
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:24,960
Legitimate masters!

332
00:19:25,360 --> 00:19:26,960
What's there to hide?

333
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:30,720
Why are you crying?

334
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:50,360
Don't laugh at me.

335
00:19:50,840 --> 00:19:52,120
I just started

336
00:19:52,120 --> 00:19:53,400
learning guitar.

337
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:55,000
I dare not play in front of crowds.

338
00:19:59,680 --> 00:20:02,000
Mind if I use your spot?

339
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:17,240
Who is it?

340
00:21:17,560 --> 00:21:18,400
It's me.

341
00:21:25,120 --> 00:21:26,440
Master.

342
00:21:34,920 --> 00:21:36,360
I've talked to them.

343
00:21:36,360 --> 00:21:37,360
You'll still live here

344
00:21:37,640 --> 00:21:38,800
and stay on the kitchen staff.

345
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:40,960
But you'll join the other kids

346
00:21:40,960 --> 00:21:42,120
to train and rehearse.

347
00:21:42,760 --> 00:21:44,360
There's a new play.

348
00:21:44,920 --> 00:21:46,640
Your acting and acrobatic skills are okay.

349
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:48,120
Now focus on your vocal skills.

350
00:21:48,520 --> 00:21:50,480
You can't just be a Wudan forever.

351
00:22:11,080 --> 00:22:13,520
Relax. Sink your breath to the Dantian.

352
00:22:13,520 --> 00:22:14,720
Tighten your

353
00:22:15,240 --> 00:22:16,200
core.

354
00:22:16,200 --> 00:22:17,520
Focus your breath here.

355
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:20,360
Don't just use your belly.

356
00:22:20,360 --> 00:22:21,720
Breathe from your chest.

357
00:22:21,720 --> 00:22:22,800
Open up.

358
00:22:23,360 --> 00:22:24,880
You know? Open up. Come on.

359
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:28,080
♪The wind howls♪

360
00:22:28,080 --> 00:22:30,440
♪So bleak♪

361
00:22:30,440 --> 00:22:31,600
Hit that pitch right away.

362
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:33,560
It falls flat right away, kid.

363
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:34,760
Your voice falls flat.

364
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:38,040
♪Horses dash, birds scatter♪

365
00:23:01,970 --> 00:23:02,840
Laidi.

366
00:23:02,840 --> 00:23:04,160
I just learned something.

367
00:23:04,160 --> 00:23:05,240
Watch me do it.

368
00:23:14,400 --> 00:23:15,240
Are you okay?

369
00:23:18,160 --> 00:23:19,000
It hurts.

370
00:23:19,560 --> 00:23:20,520
Don't move!

371
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:23,080
Let me catch my breath.

372
00:23:23,080 --> 00:23:24,320
Just let me catch my breath.

373
00:23:24,880 --> 00:23:26,520
You can't do flips all by yourself.

374
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:28,680
That's how Heiwa had his accident.

375
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:30,320
We were just kids.

376
00:23:30,320 --> 00:23:31,520
We've grown up now.

377
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:42,360
Are you okay?

378
00:23:42,360 --> 00:23:43,200
I'm fine.

379
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:44,560
I've caught my breath now.

380
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:48,480
You work really hard.

381
00:23:48,960 --> 00:23:50,640
Getting up so early to start the fire.

382
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:53,440
Practice something else.

383
00:23:53,960 --> 00:23:55,200
Stop doing flips.

384
00:23:55,760 --> 00:23:56,600
Sure.

385
00:23:56,920 --> 00:23:59,000
You... you have to teach me.

386
00:24:00,880 --> 00:24:01,720
Please?

387
00:24:07,920 --> 00:24:08,760
Do you...

388
00:24:10,080 --> 00:24:11,880
Do you take apprentices?

389
00:24:12,640 --> 00:24:13,920
Just stop doing flips.

390
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:15,600
Come on, teach me.

391
00:24:18,680 --> 00:24:20,480
If you don't teach me, I'll do flips.

392
00:24:23,680 --> 00:24:24,760
I'll do it.

393
00:24:32,520 --> 00:24:33,600
What is Dan?

394
00:24:34,880 --> 00:24:35,720
Dan

395
00:24:36,160 --> 00:24:37,960
is a red sun

396
00:24:38,640 --> 00:24:41,000
rising above the horizon.

397
00:24:41,960 --> 00:24:42,840
Dan

398
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:45,840
is the heart of the play.

399
00:24:46,560 --> 00:24:49,960
Dan is the finishing touch.

400
00:24:50,800 --> 00:24:54,920
Dan is a beacon on the stage.

401
00:24:56,560 --> 00:24:57,400
Dan

402
00:24:58,080 --> 00:25:00,160
isn't just a pretty face.

403
00:25:00,840 --> 00:25:03,240
Dan also requires acting.

404
00:25:04,120 --> 00:25:05,200
What is acting?

405
00:25:06,520 --> 00:25:08,000
It's your unique essence.

406
00:25:09,560 --> 00:25:10,400
So,

407
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:13,760
you must practice tirelessly

408
00:25:13,760 --> 00:25:15,560
and train hard

409
00:25:15,560 --> 00:25:18,040
to blend your essence and beauty

410
00:25:18,040 --> 00:25:20,000
seamlessly together.

411
00:25:26,480 --> 00:25:27,520
The bow stance.

412
00:25:28,080 --> 00:25:30,080
The right hand. Make a fist.

413
00:25:30,080 --> 00:25:31,320
- Two, three...
- Go.

414
00:25:31,320 --> 00:25:32,700
- Eyes, eyes.
- Keep this leg straight.

415
00:25:32,920 --> 00:25:34,040
Straighten the left leg.

416
00:25:34,040 --> 00:25:35,280
- Hands higher.
- Not like this!

417
00:25:35,280 --> 00:25:36,560
Use your waist. Your expression.

418
00:25:51,560 --> 00:25:53,000
One, two, one.

419
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:54,920
One, two, one. One...

420
00:25:55,440 --> 00:25:56,440
- Go.
- Faster.

421
00:25:56,440 --> 00:25:58,160
Good. Come on, go.

422
00:25:58,520 --> 00:25:59,720
Power, power, power.

423
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:01,040
Good.

424
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:02,280
Good.

425
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:04,320
Come on.

426
00:26:04,920 --> 00:26:06,280
Three, nod.

427
00:26:06,280 --> 00:26:08,040
Don't lose your position.

428
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:09,600
Back, back, back.

429
00:26:10,030 --> 00:26:10,920
The footwork.

430
00:26:10,920 --> 00:26:11,920
- It's about finesse.
- With me.

431
00:26:11,920 --> 00:26:13,640
Girl, faster. Faster.

432
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:39,880
Straighten up. Go.

433
00:26:40,200 --> 00:26:41,200
- Go.
- Good.

434
00:26:41,200 --> 00:26:42,260
- Go.
- Good.

435
00:26:43,240 --> 00:26:44,140
- Yes, yes.
- Go.

436
00:26:44,140 --> 00:26:45,030
Go.

437
00:26:45,030 --> 00:26:45,920
Good.

438
00:26:45,920 --> 00:26:46,760
Good.

439
00:26:49,320 --> 00:26:50,160
Much better.

440
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:52,280
My frozen shoulder is acting up.

441
00:26:53,520 --> 00:26:54,560
Feels so good.

442
00:26:56,200 --> 00:26:57,640
What kind of technique is this?

443
00:26:57,640 --> 00:26:58,480
Jijifeng.

444
00:27:01,640 --> 00:27:03,960
I heard the guys in your cell line up

445
00:27:03,960 --> 00:27:05,720
shirtless every night, waiting for you

446
00:27:05,720 --> 00:27:06,720
to tap their backs.

447
00:27:07,360 --> 00:27:09,800
The vet's acupoints plus my technique.

448
00:27:09,800 --> 00:27:11,560
Those guys are used to it.

449
00:27:11,560 --> 00:27:13,120
They ache all over if I skip a few days.

450
00:27:14,760 --> 00:27:16,160
That sounds like a hassle.

451
00:27:16,160 --> 00:27:18,080
If you leave, no one will tap my back.

452
00:27:19,800 --> 00:27:21,360
Ma Wuqi can do it now too.

453
00:27:21,780 --> 00:27:22,650
Really?

454
00:27:22,650 --> 00:27:23,530
Yeah.

455
00:27:26,080 --> 00:27:27,280
Let me tell you something.

456
00:27:27,920 --> 00:27:29,920
Your sentence reduction was approved.

457
00:27:38,360 --> 00:27:39,360
Why did you stop?

458
00:28:26,840 --> 00:28:28,000
(Beishan to Ningzhou)
We're at Erdaoliang.

459
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:30,040
Take your belongings and get off.

460
00:28:31,800 --> 00:28:32,640
I'm getting off.

461
00:28:34,320 --> 00:28:35,160
Careful.

462
00:28:39,180 --> 00:28:42,020
(Beishan to Ningzhou)

463
00:28:57,180 --> 00:29:02,580
(Beishan to Ningzhou)

464
00:29:03,540 --> 00:29:06,860
(Entrance Guard)

465
00:29:06,880 --> 00:29:08,840
Morning, Master Gou.

466
00:29:09,920 --> 00:29:10,880
Morning.

467
00:29:12,080 --> 00:29:13,720
I have good news for you.

468
00:29:14,520 --> 00:29:17,120
I talked to the Head of Security Section.

469
00:29:17,400 --> 00:29:19,920
You won't need to guard the gate anymore.

470
00:29:19,920 --> 00:29:22,760
Focus on rehearsing with the other masters.

471
00:29:23,400 --> 00:29:24,400
Don't worry about it.

472
00:29:24,400 --> 00:29:25,640
I'm not going anywhere.

473
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:26,720
The gatehouse is fine.

474
00:29:27,120 --> 00:29:27,960
Why?

475
00:29:28,360 --> 00:29:29,520
I feel settled here.

476
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:32,960
Used to living here, huh?

477
00:29:33,640 --> 00:29:34,480
All right.

478
00:29:34,520 --> 00:29:35,920
Do what makes you feel settled.

479
00:29:36,800 --> 00:29:37,880
A few words.

480
00:29:38,880 --> 00:29:40,120
The kids in our troupe

481
00:29:40,120 --> 00:29:41,680
have been rehearsing for a while.

482
00:29:42,800 --> 00:29:45,320
What do you think of Chu Jiahe?

483
00:29:46,320 --> 00:29:47,280
Brain, fast.

484
00:29:47,560 --> 00:29:48,880
Eyes, lively.

485
00:29:48,880 --> 00:29:49,960
Skills, shaky.

486
00:29:51,440 --> 00:29:52,440
What about Yi Qing'e?

487
00:29:52,440 --> 00:29:53,640
Brain, slow.

488
00:29:53,640 --> 00:29:54,800
Eyes, bright.

489
00:29:54,800 --> 00:29:55,840
Skills, solid.

490
00:29:56,920 --> 00:29:59,720
How are their vocal skills?

491
00:30:00,400 --> 00:30:02,120
Chu Jiahe has a good pitch.

492
00:30:02,520 --> 00:30:04,240
Sweet voice, but narrow range.

493
00:30:05,040 --> 00:30:07,000
Yi Qing'e sings crisply.

494
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:09,680
Broad and loud voice.

495
00:30:10,760 --> 00:30:13,280
For Yang Men Nyu Jiang,

496
00:30:13,280 --> 00:30:15,360
our troupe will start rehearsals soon.

497
00:30:16,200 --> 00:30:17,200
I was thinking,

498
00:30:17,200 --> 00:30:19,440
for the role of Mu Guiying...

499
00:30:19,440 --> 00:30:20,360
Yi Qing'e.

500
00:30:27,840 --> 00:30:29,360
Personal feelings aside,

501
00:30:29,880 --> 00:30:31,560
among the kids in the troupe,

502
00:30:32,120 --> 00:30:33,640
to play Mu Guiying,

503
00:30:33,640 --> 00:30:35,040
Yi Qing'e is number one.

504
00:30:35,040 --> 00:30:36,200
Chu Jiahe is second.

505
00:30:36,200 --> 00:30:38,000
There are no small roles.

506
00:30:38,800 --> 00:30:41,000
Isn't Qi Niang's role also important?

507
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:42,040
Wouldn't Qing'e fit?

508
00:30:42,040 --> 00:30:44,120
Is it because she's from Cunjia Troupe?

509
00:30:45,640 --> 00:30:46,800
That's not the main reason.

510
00:30:46,800 --> 00:30:48,360
Then what is it?

511
00:30:50,240 --> 00:30:51,120
We'll talk about it

512
00:30:51,120 --> 00:30:51,960
at the meeting.

513
00:31:02,100 --> 00:31:09,100
(Cast for Yang Men Nyu Jiang)

514
00:31:09,200 --> 00:31:10,720
Why isn't Master Qiu here yet?

515
00:31:11,000 --> 00:31:12,680
He went for groceries. No need to wait.

516
00:31:16,960 --> 00:31:20,320
As for the generals' opera
armor, how many sets

517
00:31:20,320 --> 00:31:21,360
are we short of?

518
00:31:22,800 --> 00:31:24,400
Eleven for the female generals.

519
00:31:25,080 --> 00:31:26,960
Two for Meng Liang and Jiao Zan.

520
00:31:26,960 --> 00:31:29,160
One is enough for the enemy general.

521
00:31:34,280 --> 00:31:35,440
I agree that

522
00:31:36,360 --> 00:31:38,280
Yi Qing'e is best suited for Mu Guiying.

523
00:31:40,160 --> 00:31:43,040
We can ignore the Cunjia Troupe issue

524
00:31:43,040 --> 00:31:45,200
and not care about those kids

525
00:31:45,200 --> 00:31:46,960
fighting over roles.

526
00:31:47,800 --> 00:31:49,160
Right now, for

527
00:31:49,800 --> 00:31:51,000
the opera armor,

528
00:31:51,000 --> 00:31:52,240
we are 14 sets short.

529
00:31:53,960 --> 00:31:57,120
We only have two sets, both ruined.

530
00:31:58,000 --> 00:31:59,400
We can't just let the kids

531
00:31:59,400 --> 00:32:00,880
wear modern clothes

532
00:32:00,880 --> 00:32:02,680
to play ancient people on stage, can we?

533
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:08,080
I don't get what you mean.

534
00:32:08,640 --> 00:32:10,840
If Chu Jiahe plays Mu Guiying,

535
00:32:10,840 --> 00:32:12,120
will the issue be solved?

536
00:32:16,160 --> 00:32:17,280
Chu Jiahe's dad

537
00:32:17,280 --> 00:32:19,920
is the Deputy County Magistrate for finance.

538
00:32:22,480 --> 00:32:23,480
So?

539
00:32:23,480 --> 00:32:24,720
Magistrate Chu said

540
00:32:25,320 --> 00:32:29,040
he'll solve the troupe's costume funding.

541
00:32:30,560 --> 00:32:31,440
As a father,

542
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:34,560
he also told me very tactfully

543
00:32:34,560 --> 00:32:37,720
to have the troupe value Jiahe more.

544
00:32:38,880 --> 00:32:41,080
I think it's understandable.

545
00:32:41,350 --> 00:32:42,200
Right?

546
00:32:42,200 --> 00:32:43,120
Let me ask you.

547
00:32:44,120 --> 00:32:45,640
Who's greater, the county leader

548
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:47,160
or Heaven?

549
00:32:48,680 --> 00:32:51,120
I really don't follow you.

550
00:32:52,040 --> 00:32:54,280
On our first day of learning opera,

551
00:32:54,280 --> 00:32:56,160
what the master taught us was that

552
00:32:56,160 --> 00:32:58,680
the play is greater than Heaven.

553
00:32:58,680 --> 00:33:00,240
But without costumes,

554
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:02,080
how can they perform? Which matters more?

555
00:33:02,720 --> 00:33:04,240
Still, we can't stoop so low

556
00:33:04,240 --> 00:33:05,680
just for costumes.

557
00:33:05,680 --> 00:33:06,720
Here's what I think.

558
00:33:07,480 --> 00:33:09,160
Set a piece for the two kids.

559
00:33:09,880 --> 00:33:11,680
Let them perform, then we'll decide.

560
00:33:11,680 --> 00:33:12,520
Will that work?

561
00:33:15,240 --> 00:33:16,280
I think it will.

562
00:33:24,120 --> 00:33:24,960
Qing'e.

563
00:33:25,560 --> 00:33:26,880
Master Gou is looking for you.

564
00:33:27,360 --> 00:33:28,480
Okay, got it.

565
00:33:28,740 --> 00:33:38,370
♪My lady♪

566
00:33:39,080 --> 00:33:40,680
Master, you wanted to see me?

567
00:33:46,960 --> 00:33:48,960
The troupe is staging Yang Men Nyu Jiang.

568
00:33:48,960 --> 00:33:51,440
Mu Guiying will be you or Chu Jiahe.

569
00:33:52,080 --> 00:33:53,680
Master Gu picked a scene that tests

570
00:33:53,680 --> 00:33:55,160
singing, reciting, acting and acrobatics.

571
00:33:55,680 --> 00:33:56,800
You both act it out.

572
00:33:57,200 --> 00:33:58,160
We all watch.

573
00:33:59,120 --> 00:34:00,240
I've highlighted it for you.

574
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:03,360
Memorize your lines and lyrics early.

575
00:34:04,040 --> 00:34:05,080
Okay, I got it.

576
00:34:06,080 --> 00:34:06,920
Also,

577
00:34:07,360 --> 00:34:09,280
run lines with Feng Xiaoxiao

578
00:34:09,520 --> 00:34:10,920
and think carefully

579
00:34:10,920 --> 00:34:12,360
about how to perform.

580
00:34:25,560 --> 00:34:27,120
In this scene,

581
00:34:27,120 --> 00:34:29,480
after all the Yang family men died in battle,

582
00:34:29,800 --> 00:34:31,800
Mu Guiying's son, Yang Wenguang, became

583
00:34:31,800 --> 00:34:33,360
the only man left in the family.

584
00:34:33,920 --> 00:34:36,880
He wants to go to battle
with the female generals.

585
00:34:36,880 --> 00:34:37,840
But he's too young.

586
00:34:37,840 --> 00:34:38,880
She Taijun disagrees.

587
00:34:38,880 --> 00:34:40,280
She asks him to duel Mu Guiying.

588
00:34:40,640 --> 00:34:41,960
If he defeats her,

589
00:34:41,960 --> 00:34:43,200
he can go to battle.

590
00:35:27,680 --> 00:35:29,240
Twenty-nine.

591
00:35:32,680 --> 00:35:33,520
Careful.

592
00:35:33,720 --> 00:35:34,560
Look.

593
00:35:34,840 --> 00:35:35,680
What's this?

594
00:35:35,880 --> 00:35:36,720
What?

595
00:35:38,570 --> 00:35:39,550
A script.

596
00:35:39,550 --> 00:35:40,390
(Qinqiang Opera Script
for Yang Men Nyu Jiang)

597
00:35:40,390 --> 00:35:41,700
I know. What about it?

598
00:35:42,880 --> 00:35:43,720
Look.

599
00:35:43,880 --> 00:35:45,720
Yang Men Nyu Jiang.

600
00:35:49,760 --> 00:35:51,280
Yang Wenguang.

601
00:35:52,280 --> 00:35:53,120
Me.

602
00:35:56,080 --> 00:35:57,240
Aren't you smug?

603
00:35:57,560 --> 00:35:59,440
What kind of role is it?

604
00:35:59,840 --> 00:36:01,160
He's Taijun's great-grandson.

605
00:36:01,160 --> 00:36:02,160
Yang Liulang's grandson.

606
00:36:02,160 --> 00:36:04,200
Mu Guiying's son.

607
00:36:04,200 --> 00:36:06,080
That's a complicated family tree.

608
00:36:06,080 --> 00:36:07,200
Is it a major role?

609
00:36:07,520 --> 00:36:08,840
It's alright.

610
00:36:08,840 --> 00:36:10,480
Just the male lead.

611
00:36:12,120 --> 00:36:14,480
Look at you, so smug.

612
00:36:15,920 --> 00:36:16,760
What about me?

613
00:36:17,120 --> 00:36:17,960
You?

614
00:36:18,920 --> 00:36:20,920
I saw it on the board.

615
00:36:21,880 --> 00:36:22,800
Just like before.

616
00:36:22,800 --> 00:36:23,800
One of the crowd.

617
00:36:26,040 --> 00:36:27,440
Still an extra.

618
00:36:28,120 --> 00:36:30,400
Then who plays Mu Guiying?

619
00:36:30,400 --> 00:36:32,400
Yi Qing'e and Chu Jiahe.

620
00:36:34,440 --> 00:36:36,000
Why two Mu Guiyings?

621
00:36:36,760 --> 00:36:38,080
Director Gu chose a scene.

622
00:36:38,080 --> 00:36:40,160
He wants me to act with both of them.

623
00:36:40,160 --> 00:36:42,280
He'll probably choose one of them later.

624
00:36:44,040 --> 00:36:45,800
He's picking a mom for you.

625
00:36:47,680 --> 00:36:48,880
Which mom do you want?

626
00:36:48,880 --> 00:36:50,040
I don't care.

627
00:36:50,040 --> 00:36:50,880
Really?

628
00:36:50,880 --> 00:36:51,760
I don't care!

629
00:36:51,760 --> 00:36:53,080
- Really?
- Really!

630
00:36:53,080 --> 00:36:54,160
Don't lie to me.

631
00:36:54,160 --> 00:36:55,120
I'm not lying to you, really.

632
00:36:57,360 --> 00:36:58,520
Your mom is here.

633
00:36:58,520 --> 00:36:59,400
Feng Xiaoxiao,

634
00:36:59,400 --> 00:37:00,840
let's find a place to run lines.

635
00:37:04,080 --> 00:37:04,960
Run lines!

636
00:37:07,480 --> 00:37:09,000
I'm starting, Laidi.

637
00:37:10,520 --> 00:37:11,680
Mother,

638
00:37:12,160 --> 00:37:14,520
I must avenge Father.

639
00:37:14,520 --> 00:37:16,280
If you don't go easy on me,

640
00:37:16,280 --> 00:37:18,640
how can I fight the enemy?

641
00:37:19,640 --> 00:37:20,520
Mother,

642
00:37:20,960 --> 00:37:23,560
please go easy on your son.

643
00:37:24,480 --> 00:37:27,160
Besides, how could I ever beat you?

644
00:37:27,680 --> 00:37:38,320
♪Dear son, you softly beg to go to war♪

645
00:37:38,640 --> 00:37:43,680
♪If you have real skill, I won't worry♪

646
00:37:45,080 --> 00:37:46,680
Even the pigs are running lines now?

647
00:37:46,680 --> 00:37:48,200
♪We compete on the training ground♪

648
00:37:48,200 --> 00:37:49,640
You can run lines with them.

649
00:37:53,360 --> 00:37:57,720
♪I will go easy on you, son♪

650
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:03,560
Watch my spear!

651
00:39:09,720 --> 00:39:10,960
It's okay. I've got you.

652
00:39:11,680 --> 00:39:12,520
One more time.

653
00:39:23,680 --> 00:39:24,520
Zhou Yuzhi.

654
00:39:25,520 --> 00:39:26,360
Jiahe.

655
00:39:27,440 --> 00:39:28,280
Stage combat.

656
00:39:29,120 --> 00:39:31,080
Didn't you go practice with Feng Xiaoxiao?

657
00:39:32,360 --> 00:39:34,480
Did he go practice with that dummy?

658
00:39:35,560 --> 00:39:37,440
Did he really fall for that dummy?

659
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:40,040
No way.

660
00:39:42,670 --> 00:39:43,510
Jiahe! Jiahe!

661
00:39:43,510 --> 00:39:44,360
It's me!

662
00:39:44,360 --> 00:39:45,560
Not that dummy!

663
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:46,640
Jiahe! Jiahe!

664
00:39:47,360 --> 00:39:48,240
It's me, Zhou Yuzhi!

665
00:39:53,360 --> 00:39:54,640
Let's stop here for today.

666
00:40:00,880 --> 00:40:01,720
Mother!

667
00:40:01,880 --> 00:40:04,040
Your dear son is leaving.

668
00:40:09,360 --> 00:40:10,520
If you get hungry later,

669
00:40:10,520 --> 00:40:11,520
just dig right here

670
00:40:11,520 --> 00:40:12,600
for baked potatoes.

671
00:40:13,240 --> 00:40:14,300
- Here.
- Okay.

672
00:40:18,320 --> 00:40:19,520
Go to bed early.

673
00:40:28,750 --> 00:40:30,360
I'm already hungry.

674
00:40:41,040 --> 00:40:42,480
I saved one for you.

675
00:40:43,790 --> 00:40:44,720
Mother,

676
00:40:45,360 --> 00:40:48,720
the potato got burnt.

677
00:40:49,400 --> 00:40:52,440
What should I do?

678
00:40:54,160 --> 00:40:55,080
It's fine.

679
00:40:55,360 --> 00:40:57,440
It's still edible.

680
00:40:58,560 --> 00:40:59,400
Eat.

681
00:41:00,720 --> 00:41:01,800
But how?

682
00:41:07,760 --> 00:41:08,640
It's good.

683
00:41:10,080 --> 00:41:11,000
It's really good.

684
00:41:25,160 --> 00:41:26,360
You're still up?

685
00:41:37,650 --> 00:41:38,520
Open the door.

686
00:41:55,240 --> 00:41:56,160
Who is it?

687
00:41:56,520 --> 00:41:58,360
It's me, Chu Jiahe.

688
00:41:59,640 --> 00:42:01,000
Open the door.

689
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:02,360
I need to talk to you.

690
00:42:05,120 --> 00:42:06,240
Wait a second.

691
00:42:17,480 --> 00:42:18,480
What is it?

692
00:42:20,160 --> 00:42:21,640
Can I come in first?

693
00:42:28,840 --> 00:42:30,640
I went too far that day.

694
00:42:31,520 --> 00:42:32,400
I'm sorry.

695
00:42:33,360 --> 00:42:34,960
I was wrong before.

696
00:42:36,760 --> 00:42:38,000
Let's make up, okay?

697
00:42:41,640 --> 00:42:43,400
From now on, we'll be good friends.

698
00:42:44,280 --> 00:42:45,440
We'll shop together,

699
00:42:46,040 --> 00:42:47,000
practice together...

700
00:42:48,200 --> 00:42:49,200
okay?

701
00:42:51,840 --> 00:42:53,480
Okay?

702
00:42:56,840 --> 00:42:58,440
I'll just take that as a yes.

703
00:42:59,710 --> 00:43:00,580
Alright.

704
00:43:05,020 --> 00:43:06,940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

705
00:43:09,000 --> 00:43:11,440
Fire breathing is a signature
skill of Qinqiang opera.

706
00:43:12,000 --> 00:43:13,850
He wants to spit out that very last

707
00:43:14,850 --> 00:43:15,830
mouthful of flame.

708
00:43:16,200 --> 00:43:17,320
Let's join forces.

709
00:43:17,320 --> 00:43:18,560
One lead role for each of us.

710
00:43:18,560 --> 00:43:19,470
Deal?

711
00:43:19,480 --> 00:43:22,080
Trading roles for favors?

712
00:43:22,080 --> 00:43:23,400
Selling the role?

713
00:43:23,480 --> 00:43:24,880
You learn the lesson!

714
00:43:25,190 --> 00:43:26,050
Qing'e!

715
00:43:26,080 --> 00:43:27,600
Hurry out here! Look who's back!

716
00:43:28,480 --> 00:43:29,760
How can you live here?

717
00:43:29,960 --> 00:43:32,320
If anyone's been bullying you, tell me!

718
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

719
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

720
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
♪We met and brushed past♪

721
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
♪Your shadow drifted out of sight♪

722
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
♪The stove fire blazed in my dream♪

723
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
♪Lit up the tracks of pearly tears♪

724
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
♪In my dream, water sleeves flew♪

725
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
♪Hiding a lifetime of love♪

726
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
♪The Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage♪

727
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
♪Spring water brewed strong wine♪

728
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
♪Sheep moved through the valley♪

729
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
♪It felt like a promise
from another life♪

730
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

731
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

732
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
♪If I chose again, I'd still roam♪

733
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
♪All over this sunlit plateau♪

734
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
♪The dream ends; the curtain falls♪

735
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
♪Moonlight washes off this stage makeup♪

736
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
♪The one in the mirror wears gray hair♪

737
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
♪Already sang all my joy and sorrow♪

738
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
♪Already shouted across Qinchuan Plain♪

